caption.text:
Did you know you can make $100k on Instagram as long as you average at least 2k views per Reel?

How?

There’s a popular funnel that many businesses use on Instagram today — the Manychat funnel.

This funnel works when you ask people to comment a keyword, and they automatically receive a DM from you.

It’s very important to use “Comment Me” instead of “DM me” — we’ve seen 3x higher conversions with this approach.

Another crucial point: promote your lead magnet through this funnel instead of directly promoting your services. We’ve observed a 10x difference in conversions when using a lead magnet!

So, if you use this funnel correctly, you can expect up to 5% of your Reel views to turn into monthly inbound leads (we’ve measured this after working 1:1 with over 1,000 accounts in the last 12 months).

That means if you average at least 2k views per Reel, you likely have 100+ leads on your account right now!

Of course, not every lead will be financially qualified for your offer, but with a dialed-in sales process, you can convert 5%-10% of them.

And if you’re selling a service or product priced at $1k or more, you can easily make five figures a month, which adds up to $100k+ a year.

The more views you get, the more leads, and the more sales you can make.

Comment «$100k» and I’ll DM you my new training, where I show you how to scale your business to $100k/month or $100k/year on Instagram.

In this training, I share insights after generating over $5 million on Instagram in the last 12 months.

caption.text:
DON’T DO THIS 👇

Don’t change your niche too quickly!

Do it gradually.

Let’s say you are photography niche but you want to transition into social media niche (both have been hobbies of yours but you know determined to make second one your main topic that you will grow your business in)

Here’s why you need to change your niche step by step:
A. You have your existing audience who needs time to adjust to your new topic.
B. Some of your audience may not be interested in your new topic and will unfollow (and that’s totally fine).

I recommend starting with a 30/70 split: 
- 30% content on the new topic 
- 70% content on the old topic

Then transition to 50/50, 70/30, and eventually 100/0.

For example, about a year ago, I changed my niche.

Previously, my niche was iPhone and Instagram hacks—simple, viral content to gain millions of views. 

But then I realized that high views don’t always lead to more targeted customers or revenue.

So, I decided to shift toward posting more targeted content, which could be “boring” for some of my followers at the time. 

I began with the 30/70 split.

At first, I saw a drop in engagement, but I expected that, so I didn’t panic.

What kept me calm and consistent with my new strategy was seeing income growth!

I didn’t wait for a “magic moment” like “when I start getting lots of views again, I’ll launch my product.” That’s an illusion!

I immediately began lead generation and selling my new product. I started making 5-6 figures per month.

Eventually, I reached the 100/0 stage, where 100% of my content is aligned with my new target audience.

And that’s one of the reasons I went from zero to $600,000+ a month in cash collected in under a year with a new offer—even though my views went 1 million on average to 30k

If you are thinking to change your niche because you are not sure how to scale to $100k on IG

Comment $100k 

and I’ll dm you new training where I shared my insights after scaling my business to $5mln in sales on Instagram ($3.6mln in the last 6 months)

I reviewed best sales and lead gen funnels on Instagram in 2024-2025 and explained how you can turn more followers into customers to scale your business to $100k

caption.text:
4 things I use to make my reels go viral👇

1️⃣ Popular topics VS not popular topics

If I have to choose the number one thing that affects your views the most, it is by far the topic you talk about in your reels.

For example: I can talk about How to increase engagement on your Stories, or I can talk about how to double your Reel views. Second one definitely will get more views , as this is one of the top 5 topics in my niche. Engagement on Stories is one of the top 10 or top 15 topics, but not top five.

You want to focus on your top 5 topics in your niche.

2️⃣ Visible CTA vs not visible CTA

A visible CTA means placing it prominently, either in the first line of your caption, at the end of your video, or ideally both.

One of the biggest mistakes creators make on IG is placing the call to action at the very end of the caption. In 99% of cases, most of your audience won’t even reach the end, meaning they miss the CTA.

For example, if you’re promoting something, write “Comment [Keyword] to get my new training” right at the beginning of the caption. This way, more people will see it, engage with it, and you’ll get more leads.

3️⃣ Catchy Hooks VS Boring Simple Hooks

You should spend 90% of your time when creating content on your hook! As this is the most important thing (after the topic of the video)

Here are some tips:
- Always use subtitles. The majority of IG users consume content without sound, so without subtitles, they won’t know what your content is about and will just scroll past.
- Start with a goal of your target audience. Avoid generic openings like “Once upon a time...” Say something like, “Never do this if you want X” or “Top ways to achieve Y.” The “X” or “Y” should be a result your audience desires, like losing weight, making money, growing a business, etc.

4️⃣ Converting BIO vs. Not Converting BIO

If your content reaches thousands of non-followers, you should be gaining hundreds of new followers. If you’re reaching tens of thousands, you should expect thousands of new followers.

If non-followers aren’t converting into followers, you need to optimize your bio!

Comment “BIOS,” and I’ll DM you a list of 100 bio ideas for 100 popular niches.

caption.text:
You can reach your first $100,000 in sales using paid ads

and you can also reach $100,000 using organic Instagram!

The real question is, what cost are you willing to pay? 

When you use paid ads, every mistake—whether it’s a lack of avatar knowledge or mispricing or poor sales Perfomance — costs you actual dollars. 

Now let’s say your sales conversion is not ideal so you will have to spend more on marketing to get sales you need bc your sales conversion is not good enough.

Meanwhile, your competitors, who have better sales on their side, will outspend you because they have a more effective customer acquisition process.

Same for every process you have: fulfillment, marketing, appointment setting.

Here’s why organic growth is so beneficial.

all of the challenges I just mentioned won’t stop you from scaling organically. 

While you’ll eventually need to refine all these steps, it’s easier to reach your first $100,000 organically 

because you’re dealing with a loyal audience who already knows and trusts you. 

So Even if your sales/setter team isn’t perfect, you will still have sales.

Even if your sales page isn’t flawless, you will still have sales.

If your offer is mispriced you will still have sales.

And the beauty is you pay $0 for acquiring the customer.

From every perspective, organic growth is better: 

it costs you less, your clients get better results because they are more loyal and not sceptical and ready to work, 

I’m not just saying this as advice—I experienced it myself. 

I reached my first $100,000 organically. 

Now, we make $500,000-$600,000 every month, with half coming from Instagram organic, a quarter from paid ads, and a quarter from renewals and upgrades.

Comment $100k and I’ll share with you 

My new training where I shared my insights after scaling my business to $5mln in sales on Instagram ($3.6mln in the last 6 months)

I reviewed best sales and lead gen funnels on Instagram in 2024-2025 and explained how you can turn more followers into customers to scale your business to $100k

caption.text:
Here’s how you scale on Instagram 👇

1️⃣ Use Simple Editing, Not Fancy Editing

In 99% of niches, you don’t need fancy editing. I know some of you look at my content and think, «Oh, Mike uses fancy editing, so I need that too.» But no, you don’t! The reason I use it is because I’m in social media content creation, and I also sell high-ticket offers for my brand. It’s part of my branding, and I personally love when content looks expensive. But you don’t need to copy this to be successful with your content. Even Instagram CEO Adam Mosseri confirmed that the fancier the editing, the less engagement you might get.

2️⃣ Catchy Hooks, Not Boring Simple Hooks

When it comes to hooks, you want to be strategic. You should spend 90% of your attention when creating content on your hook rather than the body, call to action, caption, hashtags, or script. Invest most of your time into creating a strong hook. 

Here are some tips:
- Always use subtitles. The majority of users consume content without sound, so without subtitles, they won’t know what your content is about and will just scroll past.
- Start with a pain point or a goal of your target audience. Avoid generic openings like «Once upon a time...» Instead, say something like, «Never do this if you want to achieve X» or «Top ways to achieve Y.» The «X» or «Y» should be a result your audience desires, like losing weight, making money on social media, growing a business, etc.

3️⃣ Visible Call to Action (CTA)

A visible call to action means placing it prominently, either in the first line of your caption, at the end of your video, or ideally both. One of the biggest mistakes creators make on Instagram is placing the call to action at the very end of the caption. In 99% of cases, most of your audience won’t even reach the end, meaning they miss the CTA.

For example, if you’re promoting something, write «Comment [Keyword] to get my new training» right at the beginning of the caption. This way, more people will see it, engage with it, and you’ll get more leads.

And follow me @instacoachmike if you want to scale on Instagram. I share daily advanced tips and strategies ✅
